## SYNC-7

SYNC-7 is the multi-node consensus engine bundled with Proteus. It queries 6 AI platforms simultaneously and resolves their outputs into a single consensus signal using a φ-weighted golden voice algorithm.

```python
# Current node configuration
NODES = [
    "claude",        # Anthropic
    "gpt4",          # OpenAI
    "gemini",        # Google
    "mistral",       # Mistral AI
    "llama",         # Meta (local)
    "custom_ggse",   # Garcia-Gonzalez Cognitive Engine (local)
]

CONSENSUS_WEIGHT = φ  # 1.618034 — golden ratio arbitration
```

When nodes disagree, SYNC-7 does not average or vote. It applies the Ollin resonance filter — the response that is most geometrically coherent with the current state vector S(t) wins.

